arcade.core.agent.module

Interface Module

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PatchModule, PatchModuleApoptosis, PatchModuleMigration, PatchModuleProliferation, PottsModule, PottsModuleApoptosis, PottsModuleApoptosisSimple, PottsModuleAutosis, PottsModuleNecrosis, PottsModuleProliferation, PottsModuleProliferationSimple, PottsModuleQuiescence

    public interface Module
    A Module object is an exclusive subcellular steppable.

    Module objects represent subcellular behaviors or mechanisms within a Cell object, such as the cell cycle or cell death. The Module should be called during the step method of the corresponding Cell object. A Module can be implemented with different versions; the specific class can be selected when switching between Module instances.

    Only one Module can be active for a given Cell object. Use Process for non-exclusive steppables.
